Key Match Events: The Cubs scored seven runs in the second inning, leading to a 7-6 victory over the Nationals.
Cody Bellinger hit a two-run homer in the second inning.
Keegan Thompson struck out Dylan Crews to secure the save.
Post-Match Reflections: Cody Bellinger expressed enjoyment in the team's recent offensive surge.
Keegan Thompson reflected on his approach to facing Dylan Crews in the ninth inning.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Cubs have scored 80 runs in their past eight games since August 22, the most in the Majors during that stretch.
Chicago has won 10 of its last 13 games and is five games back from the final NL Wild Card spot.
